                  <p>The course fee includes all essential expenses‚Äî<strong>port fees, mooring fees, fuel, tourist tax, and general yacht maintenance</strong>‚Äîso you can focus on learning without worrying about hidden costs.</p>

                  <p>Students stay onboard our comfortable, well-equipped training yacht, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/yachts/lookfar"><u>Lookfar</u></a>, which features <strong>three double cabins and one bunk bed cabin</strong> for accommodation during the course. You‚Äôll live and learn aboard from Monday to Friday, with Sunday evening boarding and Friday night stays available by agreement.</p>

                  <p>We provide <strong>tea and coffee daily onboard</strong> (alcohol not included). For breakfast, we recommend the nearby <em>Bus Stop Lounge</em>, just 200 meters from the marina. You‚Äôre also welcome to bring a packed lunch or make use of the yacht‚Äôs fully equipped galley to prepare your own meals onboard.</p>

                  <p>When ashore, you'll have access to <strong>clean shower and toilet facilities</strong> located just by the marina gate. Our base at <strong>Manoel Island Yacht Marina</strong> is in one of Malta‚Äôs most vibrant and picturesque areas, surrounded by shops, cafes, and restaurants‚Äîall within easy walking distance.</p>

                  <p>Upon successfully completing the course, you‚Äôll be awarded the internationally recognised <strong>RYA Coastal Skipper Certificate</strong>. This qualification proves you‚Äôre capable of skippering longer passages by day and night in coastal waters‚Äîbringing you one step closer to becoming an <strong>RYA Yachtmaster‚Ñ¢</strong> and opening the door to more advanced sailing opportunities and professional endorsements.</p>
